news.title: Astral to acquire 51% stake in Gem Paints for Rs 194 crore
news.para: ​​Astral has entered into a definitive agreement with Gem Paints and its shareholders after the deal was approved by its board on Friday, it said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Ambuja Cements to expand capacities to meet increasing demand
news.para: This plant has enhanced Ambuja's clinker capacity by 3 million tonnes per annum and cement sales potential by 5 million tonnes per annum, ACL said in a statement on Friday.

news.title: Telangana keen on joining hands with builders to skill locals: KT Rama Rao
news.para: KTR said such a real estate specific skilling infrastructure will create an ecosystem for the sector to thrive in Telangana as it will reduce dependence on labour from other states.

news.title: Construction equipment sales drop 8% to 85,385 units FY22: ICEMA
news.para: The earthmoving equipment segment which accounts for nearly three-fourths of the total construction equipment sales in India, experienced 14 per cent decline in growth during FY22, while road construction equipment sales were lower by 10 per cent during the same year.

news.title: Ahmedabad: 1,240 construction workers died on job in 14 years
news.para: Vipul Pandya, general secretary of Construction Workers’ Association, said that they had filed RTIs to various district and city police forces to get details.

news.title: Glitch in Nagpur civic body property tax payment portal irks taxpayers
news.para: The system upgrade has started with NMC shifting its system to geo-fencing (an application which maps boundaries by using GIS data, so only authorised person can access the fence).

news.title: Recover 90% property tax dues in this fiscal year, Haryana government tells MCG
news.para: The civic body could generate only 13% of the projected income from property tax — Rs 165 crore — against its target of Rs 1,235 crore in 2021-22.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Nod for master plan 2031 likely today
news.para: “The stage is set for the implementation of Master Plan-2031, the draft of which is ready. It will be presented before the board on Saturday. On the agenda are a total of 21 items,” said a GDA official.

news.title: Visakhapatnam: Prices fixed for middle income group layouts
news.para: The prices range between 14,000 to 18,000 per square yard for the plots in four layouts that are being carved out in Anandapuram mandal in Vizag suburbs.

news.title: Kanpur development body starts working on proposed new city plan
news.para: KDA vice-chairman Arvind Singh along with senior officials of various departments , secretary, chief engineer, OSD (land bank), town planners and tehsildar visited the revenue villages on Friday which would be included in this scheme.

news.title: Jaipur development body panel to monitor lease deed distribution
news.para: The members of the committee will go for surprise monitoring at camps, look for progress reports from officials and guide officials wherever required.

news.title: Cluster redevelopment now must for all Mhada layouts across Maharashtra
news.para: A state government resolution (GR) making cluster redevelopment mandatory in Mhada layouts issued on Thursday states that redevelopment of a single Mhada building will be allowed only in exceptional circumstances.

news.title: LIC to unlock value of its huge real estate assets
news.para: The MD of the insurance behemoth, Siddhartha Mohanty, who was in the city for the IPO roadshow of LIC, said that the state-run insurer is gradually taking back its properties. LIC has real estate assets in Mumbai, Kolkata and other metro cities.

news.title: Mumbai-based realtor sent to CBI custody till May 6 in Yes Bank-DHFL case
news.para: ​Chhabriaa of Radius Developers was arrested by the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) on Thursday. The central probe agency produced him before special judge S H Gwalani and sought his 14-day custody for further probe into the matter.

news.title: Haryana CM orders immediate MCG takeover of nine colonies
news.para: With the takeover, the civic issues of these colonies — which are currently being taken care of by the respective developers — will come under the jurisdiction of the MCG.
